[{"book_name":"Matthew","book_id":"Matt","book_order":"55","chapter_id":"3","chapter_title":"Chapter 3","verse_id":"1","verse_text":"Now in those days John the Baptist came, preaching in the wilderness of Judea, saying, 
			","paragraph_number":"3"},{"book_name":"Matthew","book_id":"Matt","book_order":"55","chapter_id":"3","chapter_title":"Chapter 3","verse_id":"2","verse_text":"``Repent, for the kingdom of heaven is at hand." 
			","paragraph_number":"3"},{"book_name":"Matthew","book_id":"Matt","book_order":"55","chapter_id":"3","chapter_title":"Chapter 3","verse_id":"3","verse_text":"For this is the one referred to by Isaiah the prophet when he said, ``THE VOICE OF ONE CRYING IN THE WILDERNESS, `MAKE READY THE WAY OF THE LORD, MAKE HIS PATHS STRAIGHT!'" 
			","paragraph_number":"3"},{"book_name":"Matthew","book_id":"Matt","book_order":"55","chapter_id":"3","chapter_title":"Chapter 3","verse_id":"4","verse_text":"Now John himself had a garment of camel's hair and a leather belt around his waist; and his food was locusts and wild honey. 
			","paragraph_number":"3"},{"book_name":"Matthew","book_id":"Matt","book_order":"55","chapter_id":"3","chapter_title":"Chapter 3","verse_id":"5","verse_text":"Then Jerusalem was going out to him, and all Judea and all the district around the Jordan; 
			","paragraph_number":"3"},{"book_name":"Matthew","book_id":"Matt","book_order":"55","chapter_id":"3","chapter_title":"Chapter 3","verse_id":"6","verse_text":"and they were being baptized by him in the Jordan River, as they confessed their sins. 
			","paragraph_number":"3"},{"book_name":"Matthew","book_id":"Matt","book_order":"55","chapter_id":"3","chapter_title":"Chapter 3","verse_id":"7","verse_text":"But when he saw many of the Pharisees and Sadducees coming for baptism, he said to them, ``You brood of vipers, who warned you to flee from the wrath to come? 
			","paragraph_number":"3"},{"book_name":"Matthew","book_id":"Matt","book_order":"55","chapter_id":"3","chapter_title":"Chapter 3","verse_id":"8","verse_text":"``Therefore bear fruit in keeping with repentance; 
			","paragraph_number":"3"},{"book_name":"Matthew","book_id":"Matt","book_order":"55","chapter_id":"3","chapter_title":"Chapter 3","verse_id":"9","verse_text":"and do not suppose that you can say to yourselves, `We have Abraham for our father'; for I say to you that from these stones God is able to raise up children to Abraham. 
			","paragraph_number":"3"},{"book_name":"Matthew","book_id":"Matt","book_order":"55","chapter_id":"3","chapter_title":"Chapter 3","verse_id":"10","verse_text":"``The axe is already laid at the root of the trees; therefore every tree that does not bear good fruit is cut down and thrown into the fire. 
			","paragraph_number":"3"},{"book_name":"Matthew","book_id":"Matt","book_order":"55","chapter_id":"3","chapter_title":"Chapter 3","verse_id":"11","verse_text":"``As for me, I baptize you with water for repentance, but He who is coming after me is mightier than I, and I am not fit to remove His sandals; He will baptize you with the Holy Spirit and fire. 
			","paragraph_number":"3"},{"book_name":"Matthew","book_id":"Matt","book_order":"55","chapter_id":"3","chapter_title":"Chapter 3","verse_id":"12","verse_text":"``His winnowing fork is in His hand, and He will thoroughly clear His threshing floor; and He will gather His wheat into the barn, but He will burn up the chaff with unquenchable fire." 
			","paragraph_number":"3"},{"book_name":"Matthew","book_id":"Matt","book_order":"55","chapter_id":"3","chapter_title":"Chapter 3","verse_id":"13","verse_text":"Then Jesus arrived from Galilee at the Jordan coming to John, to be baptized by him. 
			","paragraph_number":"3"},{"book_name":"Matthew","book_id":"Matt","book_order":"55","chapter_id":"3","chapter_title":"Chapter 3","verse_id":"14","verse_text":"But John tried to prevent Him, saying, ``I have need to be baptized by You, and do You come to me?" 
			","paragraph_number":"3"},{"book_name":"Matthew","book_id":"Matt","book_order":"55","chapter_id":"3","chapter_title":"Chapter 3","verse_id":"15","verse_text":"But Jesus answering said to him, ``Permit it at this time; for in this way it is fitting for us to fulfill all righteousness." Then he permitted Him. 
			","paragraph_number":"3"},{"book_name":"Matthew","book_id":"Matt","book_order":"55","chapter_id":"3","chapter_title":"Chapter 3","verse_id":"16","verse_text":"After being baptized, Jesus came up immediately from the water; and behold, the heavens were opened, and he saw the Spirit of God descending as a dove and lighting on Him, 
			","paragraph_number":"3"},{"book_name":"Matthew","book_id":"Matt","book_order":"55","chapter_id":"3","chapter_title":"Chapter 3","verse_id":"17","verse_text":"and behold, a voice out of the heavens said, ``This is My beloved Son, in whom I am well-pleased." 
		
		","paragraph_number":"3"}]
